Column.value: \brief This function configures packer test mode. \details This function configures packer test mode, including 4 modes (fixed data, sinewave, incremental data and prbs7). This function will be called by RFE API when user wants to configure data interface to testing mode. \pre NIL. \param [in] selectTestMode - selection among the 4 test modes \param [in] fixedTestData - fixed data to be sent if rfeHwPacker_testMode_fixedData_e is selected. For other modes, this input param has no effect and it's recommended to set it to 0ul. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfe_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

Column.value: \brief This function programs SW fields into metadata long packet. \details This function programs SW fields into metadata long packet. User can program 4x32 bit fields. This function will be internally called by main FSM to place software defined fields in the metadata long packet. \pre enableMetadataPacket has been set to true by calling function rfeHwPacker_configDataOutFormat. \param [in] swMetaData0 - 32-bit user-defined metadata0 \param [in] swMetaData1 - 32-bit user-defined metadata1 \param [in] swMetaData2 - 32-bit user-defined metadata2 \param [in] swMetaData3 - 32-bit user-defined metadata3 \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfe_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

Column.value: \brief This function configures the data output format. \details This function configures the data output format, including data group mode, enabling/disabling header and footer, and metadata long packet related settings. Metadata CRC is by default enabled in this function. This function needs to be called by RFE API. \pre NIL \param [in] enableInterleaving - If true, ADC data is grouped as interleaving mode \param [in] enableHeader - If true, header is enabled \param [in] enableFooter - If true, footer is enabled \param [in] enableMetadataPacket - If true, the metadata long packet is enabled (software meta data is included) \param [in] enableMetadataPacketHwFields - If true, hardware meta data is included in the metadata long packet. To enable the hardware meta data, \p enableMetadataPacket also needs to be enabled. \param [in] metadataPacketVirtualChannel - Selection of virtual channel used for metadata long packet transmission \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfe_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

Column.value: \brief This function configures the data output destination. \details This function configures the data output destination. There are four data output paths: CSI2, Packet Processor, CSI2 + Packet Processor, and WDMA. This function needs to be called by RFE API. \pre NIL \param [in] dataOutputDestination - Selection of data output destination \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfe_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

Column.value: \brief This function configures virtual channel settings. \details This function enables/disables each virtual channels. There are four virtual channels and individual virtual channel can be disabled. This function also sets if frame counter is cleared at the end of frame. This function needs to be called by RFE initialization function. Please note this function only enable/disable each virtual channel. Time engine will decide which profile uses which virtual channel. \pre NIL \param [in] enableVirtualChannel0 - If true, virtual channel0 is enabled \param [in] enableVirtualChannel1 - If true, virtual channel1 is enabled \param [in] enableVirtualChannel2 - If true, virtual channel2 is enabled \param [in] enableVirtualChannel3 - If true, virtual channel3 is enabled \param [in] clearFrameCounter - If true, frame counter is cleared at the end of frame \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfe_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL
